(probe_set_wco — set current WCS origin from probed XY values)
(Accounts for active WCS rotation R so the new origin lands correctly)
(in rotated frames. With R=0 this is identical to the legacy form)
(  G10 L2 P#5220 X[x_p + workspace_x] Y[y_p + workspace_y].)
(For rotated frames it shifts the origin along the rotated WCS axes:)
(  new_X = workspace_x + x_p*COS[R] - y_p*SIN[R])
(  new_Y = workspace_y + x_p*SIN[R] + y_p*COS[R])
(Args: 1 = x probed value in current rotated WCS)
(      2 = y probed value in current rotated WCS)
(Pass 0 for axes that should not move. Z is unaffected by XY rotation —)
(use plain G10 L2 for Z-only writes.)

o<probe_set_wco> sub
  #<x_p> = #1
  #<y_p> = #2
  #<wcs> = #5220
  #<wsx> = #[5201 + [20 * #<wcs>]]
  #<wsy> = #[5202 + [20 * #<wcs>]]
  #<rot> = #[5210 + [20 * #<wcs>]]
  G10 L2 P#<wcs> X[#<wsx> + #<x_p> * COS[#<rot>] - #<y_p> * SIN[#<rot>]] Y[#<wsy> + #<x_p> * SIN[#<rot>] + #<y_p> * COS[#<rot>]]
o<probe_set_wco> endsub

M2
